sentences: Emanuel Paul (February 2, 1904 – May 23, 1988) was an American jazz tenor saxophonist.
Paul did not begin playing music until late in his youth, picking up violin at age 18 and then switching to banjo in the middle of the 1920s, before settling on tenor saxophone in the 1930s.
